==English==
===Etymology===
From the French, from the Middle French ''[[novel]].'' It was recognized as English in 1828.

===Adjective===
'''neuveau'''

#New, fashionable.

===Derived forms===
*[[art nouveau]]
*[[nouveau riche]]

